COPS
in Alldays outside Louis Trichardt are cautioning community members around
Alldays and adjacent farms to be extra careful as seven lions are on the loose. The
lions have reportedly escaped from their cage in the local Ingogo Safaris,
possibly last night. .Limpopo cops spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo
said the lions were allegedly spotted by community members roaming the area
opposite Speaker Park Phase 1 and 2 in Alldays policing area, early on Tuesday
morning at around 7am. He
saidÂ the farm owner and the cops have already summoned officials from
LEDET and are currently on the way to the area. It
is not clear at this stage how the lions managed to escape.